fy-teenage-lark-94401/|title=\u2018The Kings of Summer\u2019 Review: A Giddy, Goofy Teenage Lark|accessdate=October 16, 2016|date=May 29, 2013|work=[[TheWrap]]|author=Duralde, Alonso}}</ref> ''[[The Watch (2012 film)|The Watch]]'' (as [[Vince Vaughn]]'s daughter);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2012/08/06/watch-review|title=The Watch|accessdate=October 16, 2016|date=August 6, 2012|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|author=Schwarzbaum, Lisa}}</ref> and ''[[Red Widow]]''.<ref name=EMM>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxim.com/todays-girl/erin-moriarty |title=Erin Moriarty |accessdate=November 26, 2013 |date=May 28, 2013 |work=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203222413/http://www.maxim.com/todays-girl/erin-moriarty |archivedate=December 3, 2013 |df=mdy }}</ref> She had a recurring role on [[True Detective (season 1)|season 1]] of ''[[True Detective (TV series)|True Detective]]'' as Audrey Hart,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/true-detectiver-erin-moriarty-new-lines-crawlspace-1201128737/|title=\u2018True Detective\u2019s\u2019 Erin Moriarty to Star in New Line\u2019s \u2018Crawlspace\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE)|accessdate=April 5, 2014|date=March 10, 2014|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|author=Kroll, Justin}}</ref> the problem child of [[Woody Harrelson]]'s character.<ref name=EM&DYTOISMLLL/> She appeared in ''[[Blood Father]]'', a 2016 film starring [[Mel Gibson]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/erin-moriarty-mel-gibson-in-bloodfather-1201163464/ |title=Erin Moriarty to Co-Star With Mel Gibson in Blood Father |publisher=Variety |date=April 24, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2014}}</ref> Her role as Gibson's daughter in ''Blood Father'' received praise from critics such as [[Manohla Dargis]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/26/movies/blood-father-review-mel-gibson.html|title=Review: In \u2018Blood Father,\u2019 Mel Gibson Plays With Pulp Fiction|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-08-25|work=[[The New York Times]]|author=Dargis, Manohla}}</ref> [[Alonso Duralde]] of [[TheWrap]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/blood-father-review/|title=\u2018Blood Father\u2019 Karlovy Vary Review: Mel Gibson Strikes Grindhouse Gold|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-07-02|publisher=[[TheWrap]]|author=Duralde, Alonso}}</ref> and [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/cannes-mel-gibson-blood-father-1201780294/|title=Cannes Film Review: \u2018Blood Father\u2019|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-05-21|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|author=Gleiberman, Owen}}</ref> but [[Ignatiy Vishnevetsky]] of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' felt she was unconvincing<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/review/mel-gibson-attempts-action-comedy-comeback-blood-f-240937|title=Mel Gibson attempts an action-comedy comeback in Blood Father|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-08-11|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|author=Vishnevetsky, Ignatiy}}</ref> and [[Allen Salkin]] of the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' felt she was overshadowed by the likes of Gibson and [[William H. Macy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/mel-gibson-returns-leading-man-form-blood-father-review-article-1.2758205|title=Mel Gibson returns in 'Blood Father' with chance for another ride through revenge thriller genre: movie review|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-08-19|work=[[New York Daily News]]|author=Salkin, Allen}}</ref> In September 2014, Erin Moriarty was named one of the best actors under twenty years of age by [[IndieWire]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Staff|first1=The Playlist|title=On The Rise: 20 Actors To Watch That Are Under 20|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2014/09/on-the-rise-20-actors-to-watch-that-are-under-20-272876/|website=[[IndieWire]]|accessdate=February 16, 2017}}</ref> In ''[[Captain Fantastic (film)|Captain Fantastic]]'', she plays the love interest of [[George MacKay (actor)|George MacKay]]'s character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4379475/father-doesnt-always-know-best-in-captain-fantastic/|title=Father Doesn\u2019t Always Know Best In Captain Fantastic|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-06-23|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|author=Zacharek, Stephanie}}</ref> In season one of ''[[Jessica Jones (TV series)|Jessica Jones]]'', Moriarty played a college student with a difficult life.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/125455-who-is-hope-shlottman-on-jessica-jones-erin-moriarty-gives-our-hero-a-new-mission|title=Who Is Hope Shlottman On 'Jessica Jones'? Erin Moriarty Gives Our Hero A New Mission|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2015-11-23|work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]|author=Narasaki, Rosie}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, she was cast in the [[LD Entertainment]] feature film ''[[The Miracle Season]]'' along with [[Danika Yarosh]] and [[Helen Hunt]].<ref name=EM&DYTOISMLLL>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/06/erin-moriarty-danika-yarosh-live-like-line-movie-hiroyuki-sanad-sony-movie-life-1201778526/|title=Erin Moriarty & Danika Yarosh Team On Inspirational Sports Movie \u2018Live Like Line\u2019|accessdate=2016-10-16|date=2016-06-23|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Busch, Anita}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2017, she was cast as [[List of The Boys characters|Annie January / Starlight]] in ''[[The Boys (2019 TV series)|The Boys]]'', [[Amazon Studios]] adaptation of [[Garth Ennis]] and [[Darick Robertson|Darick Robertson's]] comic book [[The Boys (comics)|of the same name]].<ref name=EM&THEBOYS>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/the-boys-erin-moriarty-cast-amazon-superhero-drama-series-comic-book-1202229406/|title=\u2018The Boys\u2019: Erin Moriarty Cast In Amazon\u2019s Superhero Drama Series Based On Comic Book|accessdate=2018-01-18|date=2017-12-18|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Andreeva, Nellie & Petski, Denise}}</ref> The series was released July 2019, and was renewed for a second season.<ref name=\"S2Renewal\">{{cite web|last=Petski|first=Denise|title='The Boys' Renewed For Season 2 By Amazon; Aya Cash Closes Deal As Stormfront|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/the-boys-renewed-season-2-amazon-aya-cash-closes-deal-stormfront-1202649409/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=July 19, 2019|date=July 19, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, Moriarty also had a starring role in the film ''[[Driven (2018 film)|Driven]]'' about the sting operation which brought down auto mogul [[John DeLorean]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[The Watch (2012 film)|The Watch]]'' || Chelsea McAllister|| \n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[The Kings of Summer]]'' || Kelly || \n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[After the Dark]]'' || Vivian || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Blood Father]]'' || Lydia Link || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Captain Fantastic (film)|Captain Fantastic]]'' || Claire McCune  || Nominated\u2014[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]] <br />Nominated\u2014[[Seattle Film Critics Society|Seattle Film Critics Society Award for Best Ensemble Cast]]\n|-\n| 2016 || ''Within'' || Hannah Alexander || \n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]'' || Bar Guest #3 || Cameo\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[The Miracle Season]]'' || Kelley Fliehler||\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[The Extraordinary Journey of the Fakir]]'' || Marie Rivi\u00e8re || \n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Driven (2018 film)|Driven]]'' || Katy Connors ||\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Monster Party (film)|Monster Party]]'' || Alexis Dawson ||\n|-\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[One Life to Live]]'' || Whitney Bennett|| 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'' || Dru || Episode: \"Flight\"\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Red Widow]]'' || Natalie Walraven || Main role; 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[True Detective (TV series)|True Detective]]'' || Audrey Hart|| 3 episodes\n|-\n|